tokens.name: Render Cut-Up B05
tokens.description:
Render Cut-ups, 2023
Collection of 48x 1/1s, 2666x4000px PNG

Cut-ups is a collection of excerpts (cropped details, extreme zooms) from ongoing sketches with 3D software (Blender). Working with generative geometric models that range from hard, architectural forms to organic surfaces, I use rendering as a way to "photograph" them - both in the sense of documentation and as a means of creating new visual compositions.

Cut-ups don't convey a sense of the actual composition, rather they are isolated details cut out of high-resolution images. This reflects the process of "discovery" through setting up (artificial) lights and cameras, geometries and textures -  only to be captivated by unexpected details and the in-between things. 

It might be the optical delights of photorealistic rendering engines, used all wrong. Or finding glitches in my geometry, bad code that has produced faulty constructs that in the end turn out more interesting. Cut-ups is a collection of these visual moments.

Marius Watz @mariuswatz

tokens.name: Geometry Dreams Z03 (Legowelt)
tokens.description:
Geometry Dreams is a series of experiments in perceptual space, a term used in architecture to describe how a space is experienced from a fixed viewpoint. It diverges from actual physical space, because perception can be manipulated by environmental factors.

The inspiration for this project comes from the many hours spent in 3D modeling software, editing complex geometries at a micro level. Zoomed in, there is a tendency to lose one's sense of the overall geometry. Local constellations of vertices and triangles present as microspaces in themselves, abstracted and broken up. 

Using 3D models from my archives of generative sketches, Geometry Dreams are rendered snapshots of such accidental spaces. Color manipulated to further enhance the sense of perceptual space, depth cues of lights and shading are sometimes distorted until the image becomes a color field. Other images, more true to their origin as rendering, depict structures with an aesthetic that might be described as "Algo Brutalism".

2023, 4500x6000px PNG, Marius Watz @mariuswatz

Abstract01 - Marius Watz, 2003

Still from interactive drawing tool written in Processing in 2003. Created for the Abstraction Now exhibition at Künstlerhaus, Vienna. In 2010, I made a Javascript port using processing.js before it was ultimately rewritten in p5.js.

I have used Processing as my primary creative tool since 2003, and all that time the Processing community has been critical to my work as an artist.

4959x7000px PNG, edition of 25+2 AP.
